@notice Returns the Store version
 @return version This contract version (1)

@notice Returns the number of Cards maintained by this contract
 @return number 2

params.balance: The amount of tokens the purchaser owns
params.currentSupply: The total amount of minted Tokens, from all accounts

returns._0: bool True if it exists, False if not
price The Card price, in WEI

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

returns._0: metadata Token metadata, as json string base64 encoded

Created(uint256,string).notice: Emitted when a new card is created

beforeMint(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Run all the required tests to purchase a Card, reverting the transaction if not allowed to purchase

getCardCount().notice: Returns the number of Cards maintained by this contract

getCardPrice(uint256).notice: Returns the price of a Card

getCardSupply(uint256).notice: Returns the total amount of Cards available for purchase

uri(uint256).notice: Returns a token metadata, compliant with ERC1155Metadata_URI
